section.text:
Title I of the
			 Communications Act of 1934 (47 U.S.C. 151 et seq.) is amended by adding at the
			 end the following new section:

clause.text:
access, use, send,
			 receive, or offer lawful content, applications, or services over broadband
			 networks, including the Internet;

the policy
			 choices and results of global competitors with respect to access competition
			 and an open platform;
